# Testing Rules

## Required coverage

| Repo type | Layer | Tool | Minimum |
|-----------|-------|------|---------|
| Frontend | Unit | Vitest | Components, hooks, utils |
| Frontend | E2E | Playwright | Login, subscribe, product happy path |
| Backend | Unit | pytest | Service/business logic |
| Backend | API | pytest + httpx `TestClient` | All public FastAPI routes |

## Test style

- Arrange / Act / Assert — keep tests short
- One assertion focus per test when possible
- Name tests as behavior: `rejects unsubscribed user from creating institute`

## After feature work

1. Run `npm test` in affected repo
2. Invoke testing-agent to find gaps
3. Do not merge without passing CI

## What not to test

- Framework internals
- Trivial getters with no logic
- SQLAlchemy engine internals (mock `Session` in unit tests; use test DB for integration)

## Platform-specific

- Mock `platform-subscriptions` in product tests
- Contract tests: validate responses against OpenAPI schema
